<P><H1 align=center>DC151 – ADD/EDIT CCJ HISTORY</H1>
<P></P>
<P><FONT color=red><STRONG>NOTE: </STRONG>areas shown in red 
are mandatory and must be completed to proceed</FONT>            </P>
<P><H3>Applicant: </H3>Select the name of the applicant whom 
the <A HREF="HELP_MortgageTerms.asp#CCJ'S">CCJ</A> is against. Will be pre-completed if the application is only in one 
name.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Value of Judgement: </H3>How much the CCJ was for, 
details to be obtained from the applicant.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Monthly Repayment: </H3>How much is the applicant paying 
back monthly to clear the CCJ.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Date of Judgement: </H3>The date the CCJ was imposed at 
the court.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Plaintiff: </H3>The name of the party making the claim 
against the applicant.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Date Cleared: </H3>If the CCJ has been satisfied, enter 
the confirmed date of completion.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Other Details: </H3>To enable additional information to 
be collected if required.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Are there any additional CCJ holders: </H3>Note the 
details of any other party named on the CCJ.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Another: </H3>if the applicant has more than one CCJ, 
click on Another and complete the details
<P></P>
<P><H3>OK: </H3>clicking on ‘OK’ leads back to the previous 
screen.
<P></P>
